{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/64587", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/64587/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/64587/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/64587/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/64587", "id": 495443998, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU0OTU0NDM5OTg=", "number": 64587, "title": "String.find(\"\") returns 'Some(0)' when searching for the empty string; expected 'None'.", "user": {"login": "richtourist", "id": 24436997, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjI0NDM2OTk3", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/24436997?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/richtourist", "html_url": "https://github.com/richtourist", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/richtourist/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/richtourist/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/richtourist/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/richtourist/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/richtourist/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/richtourist/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/richtourist/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/richtourist/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/richtourist/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 1, "created_at": "2019-09-18T20:40:57Z", "updated_at": "2019-09-18T20:43:54Z", "closed_at": "2019-09-18T20:43:54Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Hey, Ferris. Thanks for Rust.\r\nI was surprised by the result of following code, though...\r\n\r\nfn main() {\r\n    let s = \"Ferris\".to_string();\r\n    println!(\"{:?}\", s.find(\"F\"));\r\n    println!(\"{:?}\", s.find(\"e\"));\r\n    println!(\"{:?}\", s.find(\"r\"));\r\n    println!(\"{:?}\", s.find(\"Q\"));\r\n    println!(\"{:?}\", s.find(\"\"));\r\n}\r\n\r\nI expected:\r\nSome(0)\r\nSome(1)\r\nSome(2)\r\nNone\r\nNone\r\n\r\nBut I got:\r\nSome(0)\r\nSome(1)\r\nSome(2)\r\nNone\r\nSome(0)    // The empty string \"\" is not found at index [0], the 'F' is; I expected a 'None'.\r\n\r\neg:  assert_eq!(s.find(\"\", None); //FAIL\r\n\r\nTo me, 'None' seems more suitable because, well, its not there; and 'Some(0)' seems wrong because two different 'finds' can return the same index.\r\n\r\nI confirmed this on the Stable and Nightly versions at the Rust Playground, and couldn't find any similar bug on this site. I tried looking at the source code, too, but it's way beyond me.\r\n\r\nWhat do you think, Ferris?\r\n", "closed_by": {"login": "Mark-Simulacrum", "id": 5047365, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjUwNDczNjU=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5047365?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum", "html_url": "https://github.com/Mark-Simulacrum", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url":